    %ul.tw-tabs-mobile
      %li.active
        %a{href:"#tab-citizen-updates"}
          %h3 Citizen
      %li 
        %a{href:"#tab-official-reports"}
          %h3 Official
      %li 
        %a{href:"#tab-service-status"}
          %h3 Service
    .modal-wrapper
      .em-preview-modal.modal
        .intro-video
          %iframe.video-opening#video-opening{src: "http://player.vimeo.com/video/57727292?api=1&player_id=video-opening"}
        .tour-intro
          %h2 SF72 Crisis Mode
          %h3 The city&apos;s hub for emergency response.
        .tour-intro-step2
          %p Okay, so it might not look exactly like Godzilla attacking our City by the Bay, but a San Francisco emergency will leave a lot of us wondering what to do, and how to connect.
          %p In the event of an emergency, SF72.org will automatically go into Crisis Mode, where you can access a stream of offical updates, crowdsourced reports, and a crisis map that tells you how to navigate the city. 
          %p Take a tour through SF72 Crisis Mode to better understand how to use this resource, in the event of a real (non-reptile) disaster.
          %a.btn{href:"#"} Take a tour
%ol#joyride-steps{"style" => "display:none"}
  %li{"data-class" => "alert-info"}
    .icon.icon-info
    %h4.header Incident Bar
    %p.description Announces the incident and its severity. Click on “What should I do?” to get next steps. 
    %p.index 1 of 5
  %li{"data-class" => "map-container"}
    .icon.icon-map-on
    %h4.header Street Status
    %p.description A geo-tagged crisis map that shows nearby shelters and resources, as well as hazardous or road-blocked areas – so you can find safety in your surroundings.
    %p.index 2 of 5
  %li{"data-id" => "citizen-updates-tab"}
    .icon.icon-twitter-big-on
    %h4.header  Crowdsourced Updates
    %p.description A live stream of crowdsourced updates from Twitter – so you can get a full picture of what’s going on.
    %p.index 3 of 5
  %li{"data-id" => "transportation-updates-tab"}
    .icon.icon-alert
    %h4.header Official Updates
    %p.description Up-to-date content from official city sources that will keep you informed during a crisis – so you can know exactly what is happening, when it happens.
    %p.index 4 of 5
  %li{"data-class" => "citizen-reports"}
    .icon.icon-transport
    %h4.header Transportation Alerts
    %p.description Up-to-date information about what the status of public transportation – so you can navigate the city quickly, easily, and safely.
    %p.index 5 of 5
